### Retrieve Trace Metadata in Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet shows how to get current Distributed Tracing span and trace IDs using the `getTraceMetadata()` method from the New Relic Node.js agent API. This information is crucial for understanding the flow of requests through distributed systems.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

const traceMetadata = newrelic.getTraceMetadata();
console.log(traceMetadata);
