### Shutdown Agent with Pending Data (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet illustrates the usage of the `shutdown()` API method in the New Relic Node.js agent with a flag to collect pending data. This is particularly useful for short-lived Node.js processes, such as those running in AWS Lambda, ensuring that all collected data is sent to New Relic before the process terminates. It requires the New Relic agent to be initialized.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

// ... when shutting down the application ...
newrelic.shutdown({ collectPendingData: true }, function(err) {
  if (err) {
    console.error('New Relic shutdown error:', err);
  }
  // Process has now exited
});
```

