### Set Custom Transaction Name with New Relic API (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/documentation/transaction-naming-philosophy.md

This snippet demonstrates how to use the New Relic agent's API to explicitly set a custom name for a transaction. This allows developers to define transaction names that do not necessarily correspond to application routes. Custom names are prefixed with a '/' when recorded by the agent.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');
const express = require('express');

const app = express();

app.get('/beep', function(req, res, next) {
  // Use the agent’s API to set the transaction name.
  newrelic.setTransactionName('My Cool Transaction Name');

  res.send('boop');
});

app.listen(8080);
```

