### Create Web and Background Transactions - Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

These functions allow manual instrumentation of web and background transactions within your Node.js application. They are part of the New Relic custom instrumentation APIs and help in tracking specific operations. Logging is available at the 'debug' level for these APIs.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

// Create a web transaction
const webTransaction = newrelic.createWebTransaction('Custom/Web/MyOperation', function() {
  // ... your web request handling logic ...
  newrelic.endTransaction();
});

// Create a background transaction
const backgroundTransaction = newrelic.createBackgroundTransaction('Custom/Background/MyTask', function() {
  // ... your background task logic ...
  newrelic.endTransaction();
});

// Note: Ensure newrelic.endTransaction() is called to properly close the transaction.
```

